"Overall, this review has been a long time coming.  We've routinely sipped this guy at trivia night when the mood struck, and it easily satiated that ravenous IPA craving.  When fresh it keeps a nice lightness to it, and makes it easy to return to again and again.  Put a little age on it, however, and things drop off rather quickly.  The grain bill starts to seep adjuncts, which can effectively box out some of that resinous, oily hoppiness that you're looking for.  Again, this is a nice, standard, base IPA, but it won't change much for you if you've had more than a few from the style, or from Sam Adams."
