"16 ounce can, best before date of August 2014 printed on the bottom of the can. Served in a pint glass, the beer pours a light golden/orange color with about an inch and a half frothy off-white head. Head retention and lacing are both good. The brew smells like light citrusy (grapefruit) and pine hops, and some caramel malt. Taste is similar to the aroma, but there's also some bready malt and floral hops noticeable. Mouthfeel/body is light/medium, it's a bit slick, and it's smooth and easy to drink. It's not a bad brew, but for a beer billed as a ""West Coast Style"" IPA I think it's a weaker version of one. Still, I think it's worth a try at least once. $1.99 a can."
