"I was hoping for a wallop of hops, but just got a meh IPA. Poured semi aggressively into a pint glass and ended up with an inch and half foamy white head which dissipated to nothing within a few minutes. A little lacing as it's being drunk. Straw to gold in appearance, smell of malt mainly without any hops. Taste of bitter citrus as if you licked the rind of an orange and lime, pine in the aftertaste. Sticky mouthfeel after half a glass. Finished at 7 brix which leads me to believe that the wort started at an original gravity of 1.059 and finished at 1.008 which is pretty dry for an IPA. As the beer warms pine is overtaking the the citrus. Alcohol is not apparent until the very end of the glass so it's a sneaky one. I've had better. Sam Adams should just stick to their lager which is awesome only in the northeast region of the US. Once it leaves that area, it's nowhere near as good."
