"Poured from a bottle into a shaker pint, the beer is a bright, crystal clear, goldenrod coloring with a slow, steady flow of carbonation through the body and a slim, clingy, white head. Aromas of resinous and pungent hops forward, with roasted and piney notes blending in as well. Very green nose. Flavors are roast forward, with a blast of pepper spice, pine tassel, pitch, and hints of tropical fruits in the backbone. Very light bodied, giving it a slightly sharp end feel on the tongue. The resinous and slightly buttered toast aftertaste is cleaned up fairly quickly thanks to the rapid transition in the end feel. There are some grassy and oregano notes in the aftertaste, too. Good, strong, robust flavors forward that get wiped out very quickly. It's like being shot out of a cannon."
