"Overall I thought this was a nice beer and a nice example of an IPA, it had enough West Coast IPA aspects for me to know that's what they were going for without even reading the label, it's not the best West Coast style IPA I have had, but for a widely distributed IPA from Samuel Adams I think it's pretty solid. This beer had nice drinkability, it was smooth, clean, crisp, a little refreshing, not filling, and the taste did a decent job at holding my attention, I'm sure I could drink a couple of these but any more than that and it might start to wear on me. What I like the most about this beer was the how solid it was, it didn't really seem to have a weak point. What I liked the least about this beer was that the citrus hops didn't stick out just a little more, It's not that big of a deal but I think that would make this beer just a little better. I might buy this beer again, I don't know if I'll get a six pack anytime soon, but I wouldn't rule out ordering a pint at the bar. I would recommend this as a nice easy drinking IPA, but hardcore West Coast IPA fans might be disappointed. All in I thought this was a pretty solid beer, it didn't blow my mind by any means, but I still enjoyed it for what it is and I'm glad Samuel Adams decided to brew this beer. Nice work guys, thanks for another solid IPA."
