"12oz bottle from a sixer that cost $8.99 poured into a Sam Adams perfect pint glass. I had to grab this to see what the fuss was about. I also knew beforehand that this wasn't going to be a true West Coast. I don't know why brewers insist on using this term for their IPA's when they taste nothing like a true West coast. It's really gimmicky and they need to just fucking stop already. Bright orange color, good head. Aroma clearly told me this was no West Coast and to be honest it was quite boring. Maybe there were hops there but they were so subtle. Now the flavor was nice and hoppy but it wasn't piney or dank, mostly citrus and grapefruit but it was good. This was super easy to drink and I was glad I bought a sixer but this will never approach Alpine or Green Flash or Pizza Port or Ballast Point or Stone or Russian River or Lagunitas. Never."
