"Mild pale malt start. This is punched out by a spicy black pepper hop kick. Stronger in the swallow but without much complexity. Long aftertaste. The body and carbonation is as one expects from the style."
""
""
""
"Stumbled across this at Buffalo Wild Wings. On tap. Pours a clear light amber color with an inch of frothy head. Lots of lacing.The aroma is piney with grapefruit and some dankness. The taste is much like the aroma. Grapefruit upfront followed by some piney hops. Toasted malts as well as some bread. Orange peel and pine at the finish. Light mouthfeel, but I think that's the point. An easy drinker with a good amount of flavor and hop bitterness. It's on the lighter side of an IPA, but I'm glad I gave it a shot. Overall, worth having again."
"O: Very tasty, goes down quite easily, not to filling, decent kick, excellent West Coast representation of style, this is definitely one of my favorite Sam Adams beers."
""
