"On tap at Asgard in Cambridge. Hops are definitely weak for a ""west coast"" IPA. Not a bad beer, but not a west coast IPA. Maybe an APA at best. Mouthfeel is very light. Not a lot of hop aroma. More spicy than floral. No noticable citrus at all. A good balance of sweet and bitter. Not bad overall, but not great either."
