"YEAH BABY!!!! Finally a true West Coaster IPA from Sammy A!!! The beer poured a nice clear golden color with 1/4 finger thick white head that is leaving a nice lace. The scent is fresh hops that include pine and citrus notes. The taste is a nicely balanced beer between hops and malt...pine probably is more prevalent than citrus....there is a Sammy twang to it thou. The mouthfeel is medium in body with good carbonation. Overall this is a nice addition to the Sammy A repertoire."
